3 Integrated results across MR, SMR/HEIDI, coloc and SuSiE

3.1 Two-sample MR

Integrated MR interpretation. The primary IVW (random-effects) estimate is non-significant (OR = 1.086, 95% CI 0.9351.261; p = 0.282). There is evidence of heterogeneity (IVW Cochrans Q p = 0.015), but no evidence of directional pleiotropy (MR-Egger intercept p = 0.506). Steiger filtering supports the direction Ferritin Delirium (Rx > Ry; p = 0e+00). MR-PRESSO detects outliers (global p = 0.017), but the distortion test is non-significant (p = 0.705), so the outlier-corrected nominal association should be treated as exploratory.

3.2 SMR/HEIDI

SMR/HEIDI highlights. Across 43 cis-QTL panels per trait (tissues: Blood, Brain, Pituitary, Liver, Spleen, KidneyCortex; omics: eQTL/mQTL/sQTL/pQTL), Ferritin shows a broad cis-mediated architecture, whereas Delirium retains sparse signals concentrated in a few panels. Under strict Bonferroni+HEIDI (panel-wise Bonferroni + pHEIDI 0.01 + nSNP,HEIDI 3), Ferritin retains 344 probepanel records (255 unique probes; 126 genes), Delirium retains 4 probepanel records (4 unique probes; 3 genes), and the strict cross-trait intersection is APOE.

3.3 Coloc & SuSiE

Colocalisation evaluates whether two association signals within a region are consistent with a single shared causal variant (high PP.H4) or distinct variants (high PP.H3) ?PP.H4 is the posterior probability that both traits share one causal variant in the tested window; PP.H3 indicates both traits have signals but are driven by different causal variants..
